<TITLE> Courts deny bail to Khaleda, Tarique </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, Aug 20 (bdnews24.com) Dhaka courts on Wednesday denied bail to former prime minister Khaleda Zia and her son Tarique Rahman in two separate cases filed by the Anticorruption Commission. Additional chief metropolitan magistrate for Dhaka, Md Golam Rabbani rejected Khaleda's bail plea in a case involving alleged corruption in the running of the Barapukuria coalmine. The judge said his court did not have the authority to grant bail in the case. ACC assistant director Md Shamsul Alam filed the case with Shahbagh Police Station on Feb 26 against 16 people including Khaleda and 10 former ministers. According to case details, the accused resorted to irregularities and corruption in handing over charge of the coalmine to a Chinese company, costing the state coffers Tk 158.71 crore in losses. Former finance minister M Saifur Rahman, former LGRD and cooperatives minister Abdul Mannan Bhuiyan, former health minister Dr Khandker Mosharraf Hossain, former industries minister Motiur Rahman Nizami, former information minister M Shamsul Islam and former agriculture minister MK Anwar were among the accused in the case. Meanwhile, judge Md Azizul Haque of Dhaka Senior Special Judge's Court turned down an appeal for bail by Tarique in the Zia Orphanage Trust case. The Anticorruption Commission filed the case on July 3 against seven people, including Khaleda and Tarique, accusing them of the misappropriation of over Tk 2 crore from the Zia Orphanage Trust. Khaleda was denied bail in the same case by senior sepcial judge Md Azizul Haque on Aug 18. bdnews
